300 g Tilapia
28 g Almonds, sliced
1 tbsp Red Wine Vinegar
113 g Spring Mix
85 g Red Grapes
¼ cup Goat Cheese, crumbled
2 unit(s) Honey
½ tbsp Dijon Mustard
½ tsp Garlic Salt
2 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Add honey and Dijon to a medium bowl. Stir to combine.
Pat tilapia dry with paper towels, pressing well to absorb as much moisture as possible. Season with 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) garlic salt and pepper.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then add tilapia. Pan-fry for 3-4 min per side, until tilapia is cooked through.**
Remove the pan from heat.
Drizzle three-quarters of the honey-Dijon sauce over tilapia.

Meanwhile, add vinegar and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil to the bowl with remaining honey-Dijon mixture. Whisk to combine.
Add spring mix and grapes. Toss to combine, then season with salt and pepper.

Divide tilapia and salad between plates.
Sprinkle almonds and goat cheese over salad.